data.title: Claire Voyant - Pieces Lyrics & Meanings
data.meta_description: Pieces Lyrics & Meanings: You lie in consequence / You stay as part of sympathy / Can it be you'd break? / If the thoughts and words collide / You might cry to fate / This tension's part of me / This chemistry /  / All I have ever known is in pieces of light in the shadows /  / You take, you take this honesty this symmetry / You wait, you wait for suffering / Can it be that you stay / Until thoughts and worlds collide? / You might hide but you take / You can take this whole of me / Can it be? /  / All I have ever known is there are pieces of light in the shadows /  / Tonight the wounded heart's deafening / You wait for all of these things... I believe / You live fear won't change a word for destiny / But you rain, you reign over my heart and everything /  / All that I have ever known / Are the pieces of blue in the shadows / It's like I think I was immune to the pieces of me / In the sun and in the shadow /  / Tonight the wounded heart's deafening / You live here / Won't change a word... / So just believe /  /
